{
  "name": "chapelbright",
  "description": "Tubular bells ringing chapel-bright at high noon, chiming clear with no shadow. Bell-forward tubular chimes, struck and bright with clean harmonic partials and long shining tails, deliberately NO drone — chapel-bright and bell-led, clear and joyous, all light. A low bell-ground struck soft, a clear mallet-struck lead chiming the melody forward, a higher quick descant above, a sweet rounded middle, a high small-tube ping, scattered top-tube sparkle flicks with delay echoes, a lush blooming chapel wash of overlapping tails, a joyous cascading chime cloud, a damped near-dry tap pulse, and a bright treble accent. A major @ A=432, additive only, hall reverb, never dreary.",
